<section class="program-content">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="program-content__grid">
      <div class="program-content__main">
        <div class="program-content__section">
          <h2 class="program-content__heading font-display">What It Is</h2>
          <p>BRIDGE turns high school students into education policy advocates. Participants identify real failures in their school districts&mdash;from discipline policy to curriculum gaps&mdash;build evidence-based cases, and present reform proposals to the people who actually make decisions.</p>
          <p>This is not a simulation. Students present directly to school board members, administrators, and local officials. Their work produces real policy briefs that enter the public record.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="program-content__section">
          <h2 class="program-content__heading font-display">The Problem</h2>
          <p>Education policy is made about students, not with them. School boards across DFW pass policies that shape young lives&mdash;and almost never hear from the people those policies affect most.</p>
          <p>Students sit in classrooms governed by rules they had no hand in writing. BRIDGE closes that gap&mdash;permanently.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="program-content__aside">
